Note: if you have closed the Inspector, secondary click on the object (in Desktop mode, target the object with your laser and press CTRL+R), open your Context Menu (in Desktop mode: CTRL+T), and select "Open Inspector"
1.  Double-click the "Hub" object
2.  Click and drag the title bar of the "SphereMesh Collider" component with your primary hand
3.  With your off-hand, double-click on the main "Clock" slot
4.  Drop the title info that you are holding with your primary hand into the component area of the "Clock" slot
5.  Select "Copy Component"
6.  Select "Add Component"
7.  "Transform"
8.  "Interactions"
9.  "Grabbable" - you can now grab the clock by the hub and carry it with you
10. Add a child to the Clock slot
11. Rename the new slot to "Protoflux"
12. You are now ready to proceed to the Coding Tutorial area!
